The course provides basic knowledge of complaints, patogenesis, algorithms of diagnostics and treatment as well as prevention of diseases of ear-nose-throat, head and neck. The course consists of academic lectures and practical training.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aim is to provide students basic knowledge in ear-nose-throat, head and neck anatomy, physiology, patology and functions.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student who gratuated the course: -has an overview of the symptomatology, etiopathogenesis, diagnosis and management of common ear, nose, and throat diseases including head and neck region -has an overview of the rehabilitation of the patients with ear, nose and throat disorders, particularly with hearing loss
